sys_hub_action_type_definition.copied_from_name: fix - OEHRM Add Rows Send to Exc
sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Adds one or more rows to the given table.

Inputs :

  • Connection and Credential - Associated connection and credential alias.
  • Drive ID - Unique Identifier of the Drive.
  • Parent Folder Path - Relative path from root to the folder workbook(s) resides in. Empty value points to the root folder.
  • Workbook ID - Unique Identifier of the Workbook.
  • Worksheet Name - Name of the worksheet.
  • Table Name - Name of the table.
  • Values - Values for the columns in the required rows. Refer to Microsoft documentation for more information.
  • Relative Position of New Rows - Zero based index at which given rows are added.

Outputs :

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Microsoft 365 Excel, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.


Error Messages :

  • Invalid or missing access token.
  • Invalid or missing or incorrect format of the input arguments.
  • Invalid inputs or path.
  • Requested resource does not exist.
  • Encountered an error. Check log for more details.


To use this action, the corresponding Microsoft 365 Excel connection and credential must be created and associated with the Microsoft 365 Excel Connection & Credential alias. Learn More


Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.

sys_hub_action_type_snapshot.description:
Adds one or more rows to the given table.

Inputs :

  • Connection and Credential - Associated connection and credential alias.
  • Drive ID - Unique Identifier of the Drive.
  • Parent Folder Path - Relative path from root to the folder workbook(s) resides in. Empty value points to the root folder.
  • Workbook ID - Unique Identifier of the Workbook.
  • Worksheet Name - Name of the worksheet.
  • Table Name - Name of the table.
  • Values - Values for the columns in the required rows. Refer to Microsoft documentation for more information.
  • Relative Position of New Rows - Zero based index at which given rows are added.

Outputs :

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Microsoft 365 Excel, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.


Error Messages :

  • Invalid or missing access token.
  • Invalid or missing or incorrect format of the input arguments.
  • Invalid inputs or path.
  • Requested resource does not exist.
  • Encountered an error. Check log for more details.


To use this action, the corresponding Microsoft 365 Excel connection and credential must be created and associated with the Microsoft 365 Excel Connection & Credential alias. Learn More


Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
